# 3. Canonical Concept Model

There are four separate concepts.

## 3.1 Modules
Large page/navigation sections.

Use for:
- sidebar items
- main routes
- page-level availability

## 3.2 Features
Actions, capabilities, widgets, exports, enhancements.

Use for:
- buttons
- quick actions
- embedded widgets
- premium capabilities
- provider-backed actions

## 3.3 Providers
External integrations only.

Examples:
- OpenAI
- Lusha
- CRM
- search providers

Providers are dependencies, not product concepts.

## 3.4 Entitlements
Runtime permission/availability model.

A feature is available only if:
- module is enabled
- role is allowed
- feature entitlement is enabled
- dependencies are satisfied
- provider requirement is satisfied
- credits/quota are sufficient if needed

