# 7. Frontend Ownership Boundary

This is the rule that resolves the conflict between `features/` and the entitlement runtime.

## features/
Use for:
- UI/domain implementation
- forms
- module-specific components
- view composition
- services per domain

## feature-system/
Use for:
- entitlement logic
- runtime feature resolution
- role/capability gating
- module-to-feature resolution
- feature-state hooks

## Rule
`feature-system/` is the source of truth for capability availability.  
`features/` consumes that truth to render UI.

This avoids duplicated access logic.

---

# 8. Canonical Frontend Structure Addendum

The official frontend structure must include:

```text
src/
  feature-system/
    catalog/
    resolver/
    permissions/
    runtime/
```

This folder is mandatory in the reconciled architecture.

